\documentclass[12pt,a4paper]{article}
\usepackage[margin=1in]{geometry}
\usepackage{titlesec}
\usepackage{hyperref}
\usepackage{setspace}

\title{\textbf{Introduction to HTML, CSS, and JavaScript}}
\author{Your Name}
\date{\today}

\begin{document}

\maketitle
\onehalfspacing

\section{Introduction}
Web development is the process of creating websites and web applications. The foundation of web development is built using three core technologies: HTML, CSS, and JavaScript. These technologies work together to create structured, styled, and interactive web pages.

\section{HTML (HyperText Markup Language)}
HTML is the standard markup language used to create the structure of web pages. It defines elements such as headings, paragraphs, images, links, and more.

\subsection{Key Features of HTML}
\begin{itemize}
    \item Defines the structure of web content
    \item Uses tags like \texttt{<html>}, \texttt{<head>}, \texttt{<body>}
    \item Supports multimedia elements like images, videos, and audio
\end{itemize}

\section{CSS (Cascading Style Sheets)}
CSS is used to style and design HTML elements. It controls layout, colors, fonts, spacing, and responsiveness.

\section{JavaScript}
JavaScript is a programming language used to add interactivity and dynamic behavior to web pages.

\section{Conclusion}
HTML, CSS, and JavaScript are essential for building modern websites.

\end{document}

